{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867593809,"sessionID":"ses_2860b0702ffe9Wcb8nmOnayaDo","part":{"id":"prt_d79f50004001WyH4Pq1MMTYQQm","messageID":"msg_d79f4f9d5001Grz9biMQYIZ36s","sessionID":"ses_2860b0702ffe9Wcb8nmOnayaDo","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_827f951e16c742c58847382c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Write proposal.md for the agentcube project:\n2: \n3: AR: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n4: Module: sdk-python\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: Relevant specs:\n9: --- python-sdk/design.md ---\n10: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n11: \n12: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n13: \n14: ## Package layout\n15: \n16: | Path | Role |\n17: |------|------|\n18: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n19: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n20: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n21: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n22: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n23: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n24: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n25: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n26: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n27: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n28: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n29: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n30: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n31: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n32: \n33: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n34: \n35: ```python\n36: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n37: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n38: \n39: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n40: ```\n41: \n42: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: __all__ = [\n46:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n47:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n48:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n49: ]\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n53: \n54: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n55: \n56: | Component | Resolved settings |\n57: |-----------|-------------------|\n58: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n59: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n60: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n61: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n62: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n63: \n64: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n65: \n66: ```python\n67: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n68:     def __init__(\n69:         self,\n70:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n71:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n72:         ttl: int = 3600,\n73:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n74:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n75:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n76:         verbose: bool = False,\n77:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n78:     ): ...\n79: \n80:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n81: \n82:     def __enter__(self): ...\n83:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n84: \n85:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n86: \n87:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n88:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n89:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n90:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n91:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n92:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n93: ```\n94: \n95: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n96: \n97: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n101:     def __init__(\n102:         self,\n103:         agent_name: str,\n104:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n105:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:         verbose: bool = False,\n107:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n108:         timeout: int = 120,\n109:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n110:     ): ...\n111: \n112:     def __enter__(self): ...\n113:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n114: \n115:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n116: \n117:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n118: ```\n119: \n120: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n121: \n122: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n123: \n124: ```python\n125: class ControlPlaneClient:\n126:     def __init__(\n127:         self,\n128:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n129:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n130:         timeout: int = 120,\n131:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n132:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n133:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n134:     ): ...\n135: \n136:     def create_session(\n137:         self,\n138:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n139:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n140:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n141:         ttl: int = 3600,\n142:     ) -> str: ...\n143: \n144:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n145: \n146:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Control plane — HTTP\n150: \n151: | Method | Path | Notes |\n152: |--------|------|-------|\n153: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n154: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n155: \n156: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n157: \n158: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n159: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n160: \n161: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n162: \n163: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n164: \n165: ```python\n166: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n167:     def __init__(\n168:         self,\n169:         session_id: str,\n170:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n171:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n172:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n173:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n174:         timeout: int = 120,\n175:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n176:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n177:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n178:     ): ...\n179: \n180:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n181: \n182:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n183:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n184:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n185:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n186:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n187:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n188:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) — base URL\n192: \n193: If `base_url` is not provided:\n194: \n195: ```text\n196: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n197: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n198: ```\n199: \n200: ### Data plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n201: \n202: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n203: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n204: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n205: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n206: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n207: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n208: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n209: \n210: **Headers:**\n211: \n212: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n213: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n214: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n215: \n216: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n217: \n218: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n222:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n223: \n224:     def __init__(\n225:         self,\n226:         router_url: str,\n227:         namespace: str,\n228:         agent_name: str,\n229:         timeout: int = 120,\n230:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n231:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n232:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n233:     ): ...\n234: \n235:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n236: \n237:     def invoke(\n238:         self,\n239:         session_id: str,\n240:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n241:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n242:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n243: \n244:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) — base URL\n248: \n249: ```text\n250: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n251: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### Data plane — HTTP\n255: \n256: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n257: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n258: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n259: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n260: \n261: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n262: \n263: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: def create_session(\n267:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n268:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n269: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n270: ```\n271: \n272: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n273: \n274: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n275: \n276: ```python\n277: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n278: ```\n279: \n280: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n281: \n282: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n283: \n284: ```python\n285: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n286: ```\n287: \n288: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n289: \n290: ```python\n291: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n292:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n293:     pass\n294: \n295: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n296:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n297:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n298:         self.stderr = stderr\n299:         self.command = command\n300:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n301: \n302: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n303:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n304:     pass\n305: \n306: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n307:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n308:     pass\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n312: \n313: ```toml\n314: dependencies = [\n315:     \"requests\",\n316:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n317:     \"cryptography\",\n318: ]\n319: ```\n320: \n321: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n322: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n323: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n324: \n325: \n326: --- python-sdk/spec.md ---\n327: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n328: \n329: ## Purpose\n330: \n331: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n332: \n333: ## Requirements\n334: \n335: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n336: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n339: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n340: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n341: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n344: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n345: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n346: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n349: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n350: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n351: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n354: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n357: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n358: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n359: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n362: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n363: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n364: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n365: \n366: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n367: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Context manager\n370: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n371: - **WHEN** the block exits\n372: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n375: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n376: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n377: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n380: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n381: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n382: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n383: \n384: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n385: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Create session\n388: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n389: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n390: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Delete session\n393: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n394: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n395: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n398: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n399: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n400: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n401: \n402: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n403: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Execute command\n406: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n407: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Files API\n410: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n411: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n412: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n413: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n414: \n415: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n416: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n417: \n418: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n419: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n420: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n421: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n422: \n423: ### Requirement: Session header management\n424: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n427: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n428: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n429: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n430: \n431: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n432: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Command failure\n435: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n436: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n437: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n438: \n439: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n440: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n441: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n442: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n443: \n444: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n445: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n448: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n449: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n450: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n453: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n454: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n455: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n460: \n461: \n462: Include: purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives considered.\n\n(End of file - total 462 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"prev